<|startoftext|>First time having Lenny's back in Charlotte.\n\nTucked into the corner of the mall, this quaint little place is conveniently located in an nondescript shopping plaza on the second floor of the mall in the heart of the North Charlotte mall. Great food offerings for breakfast, lunch, and even dinner.\n\nI'd recommend eating here at least once upon a visit.\n\n\nPizza is the best thing here, but my wife's lunch combo was a hit! Lots of ingredients and good size servings, with loads of meat to keep me coming back.\n\nI would recommend sitting outside and having breakfast here, along with a great view of the downtown skyline.<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>This was the only spot we went to on our trip to LA, especially since we're not that sure about Vegas. Great experience. This is just a review of the restaurant- it's a family owned restaurant- their menu (I hate that we can't make our own meals online) really is all the same. The staff there is very accommodating and will not skimp on anything on the food.\n\nThe food was good, but the service was very poor. The server never returned our request and I felt uncomfortable asking our table. We ordered tea- so big portions that they had to leave us empty handed. Instead we were served chips and salsa with chips in the cups. The salsa on the plate looked just like a slice of cheese they used to make in their Mexican lab; that was just not okay.\n\nThe chicken and waffles with blueberry lemonade was pretty good though.\n\nThe decor isn't too bad. It's very upscale with plenty of booths and chairs, and a lot of comfy chairs and tables. The booths are made from scratch and pretty comfortable, and the chairs were nice and the room was great looking, I didn't eat the food. The food was pretty good, the service was okay.<|endoftext|>
